The '''plain-backed sparrow''' ('''''Passer flaveolus'''''), also called the '''Pegu sparrow''' or '''olive-backed sparrow''', is a [[Old World sparrow|sparrow]] found in [[Southeast Asia]]. Its range spans from Myanmar to central Vietnam, and south to the western part of [[Peninsular Malaysia]].<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" />

